post_text:
In partnership with Save the Children, the Education Service Center, Region 2 is excited to announce their Summer Reading Challenge July 27th through the August 31st!

How to Participate:
Â· Read a minimum of two books per week.
Â· Families in Region 2 with children ages 0 to 12th grade are eligible!
Â· Complete a reading log for each child each week during the challenge using the flyer QR Code or link below. If it is a chapter book, log the chapter number and title. Each chapter is considered one book.
Â· Each log submitted enters a family into the prize drawing. Prize drawing is a family fun pack with games, books and more!
Â· Read more than two books? Just submit another reading log! The reading log form requires two books to complete submission.Reading Log Link/Google Form:

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdLGY5y70p6mOJm0kt9jsclhDeYzO5dIYN0iqlX7lH6540Hvg/viewform?usp=sf_link

post_text:
Summer School Reminder:
Calallen ISD will be hosting summer school July 7-23, 2020 for students who are required to attend due to failure. Students must be registered online at https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/QRTZ9MY no later than July 2nd.

For students who need to make up hours in order to earn credit, but passed all classes, families will be contacted regarding the method of delivery for each student. Students requiring make up hours will not report to the summer school campus on July 7th, and are not required to register online.

All campuses are currently closed, causing phone message delivery to be delayed.

post_text:
ATTENTION CLASS OF 2020 PARENTS

A video is being created for CHS Class of 2020 GRADUATION CEREMONY. If you would like for your senior to be included in the CHS Class of 2020 video, please email 2 pictures. We would like a picture of your child when they were in K-1 and a current picture (preferably a senior portrait). Please email pictures to rsendejo@calallen.org by Tuesday May 19, 2020. THIS VIDEO WILL BE PLAYING DURING THE CEREMONY.

In the email subject line, please type CLASS OF 2020 PICS.
In the message, please include the following statement. "By the delivery of this email I allow this information to be publicly released to recognize my senior."
Please include the seniors full name.
Please include your senior's shirt size.

1440 KEYS with Deanna Stuart: Allstate Insurance.
Paid Partnership Â·

Our Student Athlete of the Week presentation took us to Calallen High School today to recognize SR Alyssa Rodriguez. Alyssa has a 5.0 GPA (that's not a mistake), which ranks her in the Top 10% of her senior class. She hopes to sign a NLI to play Volleyball in College next month. In her free time she volunteers at Nursing Homes and has worked the past two summers at the Texas State Aquarium. Keep on making us proud Alyssa!
The Student Athlete of the Week is presented by Deanna Stuart: Allstate Insurance Agency.

â€¼ï¸ATTENTION SENIORSâ€¼ï¸
All Seniors who havenâ€™t already taken their senior pictures for the Calallen High School yearbook should visit the school auditorium on Monday, Sept. 30 before 3 p.m. through elective classes to take their portraits. There is no fee for this picture. Seniors, whether they take their pictures with the photographer at school on Monday or with one of their choice, must be in school dress code. Dress nice and smile! Senior yearbook pictures are due Oct. 11, emailed by the photographer to calallenwildcatter@gmail.com.

text: Great things are happening around Calallen ISD! Through hard work and vision from various individuals, the groundbreaking ceremony for Calallen West Elementary School took place this afternoon.

shared_text:
Calallen Independent School District added 22 new photos â€” at Calallen Independent School District.
May 13, 2019 Â· Corpus Christi, TX Â·

Calallen ISD with the help of its Board of Trustees and key Bond Committee Members broke ground for Calallen West Elementary. The new elementary will be located off CR69/Hazel Bazemore Road and will house 650 students. It is expected that it will take 14-16 months for the building to be completed. The architect on the project is RWS Architects â€“ Malcolm Gaus; Polasek Construction is the Construction Manager for this project.
